SECTION C 
Answer to Array of TravelPass Objects vs. Array of TravelPass 
Pointers:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Because we run into the slicing problem. When we cast back to a TravelPass
object, we will lose information about the derived objects. We cannot get
that information back afterwards.

Any other notes for the marker:
-------------------------------
The input method was not implemented in the TravelPass class,
but I wanted to avoid coupling the class with the user interface. I left
the management of input up to the user interface class.